Growing annuity or increasing annuity refers to the cash flow that occurs at equal intervals which increases at an indicated constant rate. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Growing annuity}&=\text{Cash flow} \times \dfrac{1-\left(\frac{1+\text{growth rate}}{1+\text{return rate}}\right)^{\text{time}}}{\text{return rate}-\text{growth rate}}
\end{aligned}$$

For the next step, we will use the concept of future value which is basically the future price of recurring payments based on a particular rate of return and discount rate. The formula for the future value annuity is given as:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Future value annuity}&=\text{Cash flow} \times (1+\text{return rate})^\text{time}
\end{aligned}$$
